eNCA's Dasen Thathiah has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG -  Search, rescue and operations are continuing in KwaZulu-Natal.  Thousands of people are still helpless in KwaZulu-Natal waiting for assistance from authorities. At least 259-people died. eNCA's Dasen Thathiah has more details. Courtesy #DStv403  At least 259 people have died so far, but that number is expected to rise. Meanwhile, thousands of people are still waiting for assistance from authorities. READ: Death toll hits 259 in one of SA's deadliest floods on record Water and power services have also been disrupted in several parts of the province. eNCA’s Dasen Thathiah shares more details in the videos above.